<subSubSection pageId="72" pageNumber="73" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="72.[151,1437,255,1255]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1191,1218]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Discussion:</emphasis>
Nothing is known about the biology of this species. Although it closely resembles 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Young &amp; Skevington &amp; Steenis" authorityYear="2020" box="[1246,1429,1192,1218]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Psilota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coerulea">
<emphasis box="[1246,1429,1192,1218]" italics="true" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Psilota coerulea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the calypter colour character appears to be invariant and is supported by DNA Barcodes.
</paragraph>
